-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/cvs-caremark-comes-under-shareholder-pressure-to-split-nyt-says.html
CVS Caremark Corp. (CVS) , which is being
investigated for antitrust behavior by attorneys from 24 states
and the Federal Trade Commission, is coming under increasing
pressure to split up four years after CVS and Caremark merged,
the New York Times reported, citing a joint letter from consumer
groups.  The groups, which include Community Catalyst, the  Consumer
Federation of America , the  Consumers Union , the National
Legislative Association on Prescription Drug Prices, and U.S.
Pirg, said consumersâ€™ interests had been harmed and the company
had used patient information freom Caremark to steer customers
to CVS pharmacies, the newspaper said.  Carolyn Castel , a CVS Caremark spokeswoman, said the
company wasn cooperating with the investigatins and had complied
fully with antitrust laws, the NYT said.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
